Cloakfox: invoke pref migration + seed sync + WebRTC sync at BrowserGlue.

Three parent-process modules invoked at _beforeUIStartup:

  1. CloakfoxPrefMigration: one-shot mirror of legacy roverfox.s.*
     prefs (pre-cpp-first extension era) into cloakfox.s.*. Sets
     cloakfox.migration.v1.done=true on first run.

  2. CloakfoxSeedSync: continuous snapshot of cloakfox.container.*
     and cloakfox.* prefs into Services.ppmm.sharedData, plus a
     pref observer that keeps the snapshot live. JSWindowActor
     children read seeds via Services.cpmm.sharedData.get since
     user-set prefs in our custom namespaces don't auto-sync to
     content processes (verified empirically).

  3. CloakfoxWebRTCSync: async fetch of the user's current public
     IPv4 from a public IP-echo endpoint, published to sharedData.
     CloakfoxWebRTC actor reads the value and calls the C++
     window.setWebRTCIPv4 setter so ICE candidates report the
     same IP HTTP shows. Network-change observer refreshes on
     link bounces (VPN connect/disconnect, sleep/wake).

Order matters: migration first (so any roverfox.s.* legacy values
land in cloakfox.s.* / cloakfox.container.* before sync snapshots
them), then seed-sync, then WebRTC sync (async, doesn't block).

--- a/browser/components/BrowserGlue.sys.mjs
+++ b/browser/components/BrowserGlue.sys.mjs
@@ -382,5 +382,40 @@

